62.content:
{
  "wood_elf": {
    "title": "Wood Elf",
    "narrative_profile": {
      "description": "Wood Elves are the reclusive, fae, and often dangerous cousins of the High Elves who remained in the Old World's magical forests. They are separatists, deeply entwined with nature and forest spirits. There are two main kiths found near the Reikland: the ruthless and xenophobic Asrai of Athel Loren, and the more politically-minded Eonir of the Laurelorn. The Asrai are sent out in kinbands to hunt the enemies of their forest, while the Eonir have established a 'temporary' camp to observe and manipulate Human politics.",
      "sylvan_cousins": "The Laurelorn Wood Elves proactively engage in politics to protect themselves, mixing with others. In character, they are more like High Elves, whilst still having the Skills and Talents of Wood Elves. By comparison, the Athel Loren kinbands prefer to hide in the shadows, shunning contact with all others, instead striking deadly blows designed to cause fear and terror.",
      "opinions": {
        "on_humans": "Seen as hateful creatures with dark hearts, but also as a widespread and warlike tool to be manipulated for the Wood Elves' own ends.",
        "on_dwarfs": "Considered more stubborn than ancient oaks, understanding only the argument of swift and decisive force.",
        "on_halflings": "Their talkative nature and thievery skills are noted with a degree of impressed caution; their companionship may be worth the risk.",
